                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, vivid red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>ሰላ፡ ለኪ፡ or ሰላ፡ ለ፡ for ሰላም፡ ለኪ፡</item>
                           <item>ሰላ፡ ለከ፡ for ሰላም፡ ለከ፡</item>
                           <item>ስብ፡ ለከ፡ or ስብ፡ ለ፡ for ስብሐት፡ ለከ፡</item>
                           <item>ስብ፡ ለክ፡ for ስብሐት፡ ለክሙ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; incipit of salām-hymns; initial words
                           and their abbreviations of each strophe; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 On the incipit page of Text I
                           (fol. 3r), few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Readings are indicated by the name of hour of the
                              day, written in black and red, probably in the main hand, decorated,
                              in the upper margin: ዘነግህ: <locus target="#3r">fol. 3r</locus>. ዘ፫ሰዓት:
                                 <locus target="#5v">fol. 5v</locus>. ዘ፯ሰዓት: <locus target="#8r">fol. 8r</locus>. ዘ፱ሰዓት: <locus target="#11r">fol. 11r</locus>.
                              ዘ፲ወ፩ሰዓት: <locus target="#14r">fol. 14r</locus>. ዘንዋም: <locus target="#17r">fol. 17r</locus>. ዘመንፈቀ፡ ሌሊት: <locus target="#20v">fol. 20v</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Crude notes written in pen on fols. 1v, 2r, 2v, 24v.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
